            "answer_text": "I agree with the answer given by Niko Rakos in technique. Here are some points in harmony. Some other points: you could use a bass note of the root of the modeuse chords that revolve around the root of the modereduce chords that revolve the original scale (from which the mode has originated)When using 4 part voices use notes that are the root of the mode, its third , or fifth as the highest or lowest note. (As long as its third or fifth is not the original tonic from the scale which the mode has been derived)",
